nodes.title: ScenePresets
widgets_values: ScenePresets - i use this to save full prompts for complete images. useful when you have a complete prompt you like.

nodes.title: Subject Presets
widgets_values: Subject presets - use this to describe the entire character, subject of the image.

nodes.title: Artist Presets
widgets_values: Artist/Photography Presets - use these to give a "style" from a specific artist - or photography/art style

nodes.title: Accessories
widgets_values: THESE are set to be "multi-select" even when on manual mode. To change YOUR categories, open the Preset Manager - hit "edit categories" and you can create a new category (requires restart) - you can reorder the way the categories are sent to the prompt builder, and you can individually set the category to single-select "radio buttons" or multi-select.

nodes.title: Pose / Outfit / Setting
widgets_values: Super fun to set to build your character, then set these all to random all and get different poses / outfits / settings.

nodes.title: CustomText
widgets_values: adds text into the image. type what you want, pick a preset, build your own presets

nodes.title: Extras Presets
widgets_values: use these basically as a suffix - mostly used for "end of prompt" style photography prompts

nodes.title: LivePreviewMirror
widgets_values: Shows WHATEVER live preview is currently active on any sampler. (must have live previews turned on in comfyui settings)

This is your main prompt combiner. 

When you create a "category" in the Preset Manager ( "PM" floating button ), once you restart ComfyUI - you'll see an input for your new category here on the console. 

there will ALSO be a new node available to you for that category. Connect that to the Prompt Builder Console. You can adjust the build order in the Preset Manager.

Add presets to your category in the Preset Manager. (will only require a browser refresh, not a full reboot)

nodes.title: Preset List - (can be filtered by metadata filter node)
PREFIX / SUFFIX
widgets_values: here you can add whatever prompt you want BEFORE or AFTER the prompt builder

nodes.title: NOTE
widgets_values: shows you the full prompt being sent to the sampler
right-click "node properties panel" turn on and off any categories you don't want sent to big display. can be used for filename too!

nodes.title: CharacterBuilder
widgets_values: use this to create the characters - randomize anything you want, or keep random mode on "manual" to choose one specifically
Connect THIS console's "positive" to your Clip Encoder going to your sampler's negative. This allows you to have a "Negative Prompt" category node populated with negative prompt presets.
